```
std::lock_guard lock(runner);
runner->wait();
```

Maybe it makes sense to use `try_call/on_copmletion` guard but see below. 

> runner->increaese_ref();
> ... // Be sure this doesn't throw!
> runner->decrease_ref();

We protected ourselves from exceptions with the following expression
```
 [runner] () noexcept { runner->wait(); }();
```
Any exception will cause termination due to `noexcept` specifier.

