Previously, we subclassed `DDPStrategy` and `FSDPStrategy`, and initialized a strategy instance with a list of init kwargs provided by the users. 

I found that we can dynamically change property methods of an instance with `setattr`, so that the users only need to provide a strategy object, instead of an argument list. We change these two property methods on our end.

```python
from types import MethodType

@property
def root_device(self) -> torch.device:
    return ray.train.torch.get_device()

@property
def distributed_sampler_kwargs(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:
    return dict(
        num_replicas=self.world_size,
        rank=self.global_rank,
    )

# In LightningTrainer's worker loop

# - Get the strategy object
strategy = lightning_config["_trainer_config"].get("strategy", DDPStrategy())

# - Dynamically change properties to our implementations
setattr(strategy.__class__, "root_device", root_device)
setattr(strategy.__class__, "distributed_sampler_kwargs", distributed_sampler_kwargs)
```

