Yes it is string undefined. 

When we run this:

```
    fireEvent(this, "value-changed", {
      value: `${this._dateInput.value} ${this._timeInput.value}`,
    });
```

If this._dateInput.value is undefined, this sets value to "undefined 00:00:00"

Then in render, we split value:
```
const values = this.value?.split(" ");
```

And so we set date value to "undefined", and time value to "00:00:00". And date picker throws an error because "undefined" is not a date (it seems happy with value=undefined, in which case it just leaves the field blank).

